White_Plains.Glenwolde Park Historic District: Glenwolde Park Historic District is a national historic district located at Tarrytown, Westchester County, New York. It encompasses 10 contributing buildings, 2 contributing sites, and 1 contributing structure in a distinctive residential enclave of Tarrytown. It was developed in 1926 and consists of a small number of attached and freestanding dwellings in the Tudor Revival, Colonial Revival, and Dutch Colonial style.
